uld not own the final web payload, publishing flow, browsing UI, or\n+review-specific copy. If those need real code in this repository later, prefer a\n+separate module or crate layered on top of `but-agentlog`.\n+\n+### Agent Handoff\n+\n+The handoff feature is expected to live in the GitButler CLI, but it needs a\n+separate design pass before implementation.\n+\n+The rough workflow is:\n+\n+1. a user asks an agent to catch up with a branch or project\n+2. the agent uses a skill and/or `but` CLI subcommands to discover relevant\n+   historical sessions\n+3. the agent reads a bounded timeline or related-session window\n+4. optionally, `but status` can hint that historical agent session data is\n+   available and point agents toward the follow-up commands\n+\n+Do not implement this yet. First keep the primitives clean enough that CLI\n+commands can be designed around them without changing storage.\n*** End Patch\n","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T15:36:55.987Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]","name":"apply_patch"}}}